I wanted to fly, since I was small.
And today it was, you know... I flew an airplane today. I haven't quite processed that yet.
Data from Flightaware.
I'm trying to go again next Saturday. The weather doesn't look too good right now, but it's also only Monday.
It's already becoming clear where the problems lie. It will probably be VERY difficult to get the medical permit due to the FAA's opinion on certain medications.
It's not impossible, but it will take VERY long and means a LOT of extra work.
That's somewhat discouraging, but still just another problem that needs to be solved. So far, it seems to be solvable. It just costs a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what's ahead of me.
The FAA is not a fan of ADHD. They definitely won't give you a medical permit if you take medication against it.
